  "prompt": "Kindly suggest the best NPTE classes in NY?",
  "response": "Finding the best NPTE (National Physical Therapy Examination) prep classes in New York can depend on several factors such as cost, location, format (in-person or online), and personal learning preferences. However, some well-regarded options are:\n\n1. **Scorebuilders**: Known for their engaging workshops and comprehensive materials, Scorebuilders has been a popular choice among candidates preparing for the NPTE.\n\n2. **TherapyEd**: This organization offers review courses throughout the country, including New York, and is renowned for their extensive review books and experienced instructors.\n\n3. **PT Final Exam**: While largely online, they've gained popularity for their flexible and comprehensive prep tailored to different learning styles.\n\n4. **IPT - International Institute of Professional Education**: Offers both in-person and online options specifically designed for NPTE preparation.\n\n5. **Edsyn**: Offers personalized coaching and small group classes to ensure students get the attention they need.\n\nWhen choosing a class, consider checking reviews, asking for recommendations in physical therapy forums or groups, and reaching out directly to these programs for any trial classes or more detailed information. It's also helpful to look into whether they offer any guarantees or support if you do not pass the examination on your first attempt.",
